body:
@kennknowles -- your root cause makes sense, and confirmed via Jenkins output.

Sanity check -- @tgroh, since I think you thought hard about this last, can you confirm whether we've decided to try to make the way errors are surfaced standardized across runners?

And as another pointer, I recently dealt with this issue and decided that `ExpectedException` wasn't powerful enough. Instead, I just did something like this:

```java
try {
   ... // failing code, e.g., p.run().waitUntilFinish();
   fail(); // should not get here.
} catch (Exception e) {
  String fullTrace = Throwables.getStackTraceAsString(e);
  assertThat(fullTrace, ... /* stuff I wish ExpectedException did */);
}
```
